Canadian Grand Prix Is Halted Because of Rain; Lewis Hamilton Crashes Out

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-06-12T18:16:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-12/canadian-formula-one-grand-prix-is-suspended-because-of-rain.html
Today’s Canadian Formula One Grand
Prix in  Montreal  was temporarily suspended on the 25th lap of 70
because of rain. Red Bull’s Sebastian Vettel was leading at the
time.  Lewis Hamilton  of McLaren crashed out on the eighth lap
after colliding with his teammate Jenson Button.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  